Program: Great Lives
Title: The A-Z of Dr Johnson
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b00mg74v
Last Broadcast Date: Fri 4 Aug 2017
Matthew Parris presents the biographical series in which his guests choose someone who has inspired their lives. Boris Johnson, the Mayor of London, nominates Samuel Johnson, writer of the great dictionary. Dr Johnson's biographer, Peter Martin, joins the discussion.